<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN308">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>poṉvārn taṉṉa puriyaṭaṅku narampiṉ</l>
<l>miṉṉēr paccai miñiṟṟuk kuraṟ cīṟiyāḻ</l>
<l>naṉmai niṟainta nayavaru pāṇa</l>
<l>cīṟūr maṉṉaṉ ciṟiyilai yeḵkam</l>
<l>vēntūr yāṉai yēntumukat tatuvē</l>
<l>vēntuṭaṉ ṟeṟinta vēlē yeṉṉai</l>
<l>cāntā rakala muḷaṅkaḻin taṉṟē</l>
<l>yuḷaṅkaḻi cuṭarppaṭai yēntinam peruviṟa</l>
<l>lōcciṉaṉ ṟuranta kālai maṟṟavaṉ</l>
<l>puṉṟalai maṭappiṭi nāṇak</l>
<l>kuñcara mellām puṟakkoṭut taṉavē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>With a bee-voiced little lute with lightning-like fresh skin,</l>
<l>with twisted strings as if overflowing with gold,</l>
<l>oh adorable bard full of goodness,</l>
<l>the little [leaf-]shaped blade of the king of the litlle village</l>
<l>was in the upturned face of the elephant mounted by the king.</l>
<l>The spear thrown in rage by the [enemy] king passed through</l>
<l>the heart in the sandal-smeared chest of our lord.</l>
<l>When, holding up the glowing weapon that had passed through [his] heart, </l>
<l>our [man of] great victory aimed [and] drove [it home], </l>
<l>his (~ that king’s) elephants all turned [their] back, [fleeing]</l>
<l>so that [their] low-headed youthful elephant cows were ashamed.   </l>
</lg>
    </div>
